se.jguru.nazgul.core.algorithms.api.trees.path

Interface Path<S extends Comparable<S>>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - The type of segment from which this Path is constructed.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<Path<S>>, Iterable<S>, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SemanticPath<E,SegmentType>

    public interface Path<S extends Comparable<S>>
extends Iterable<S>, Comparable<Path<S>>, Serializable
    Generic immutable Path, defining a single continuous list of segments. This is applicable - for example - as a Path within a Tree.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB

      • size

        int size()
        Returns:

      • get

        S get(int index)
throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Retrieves the path segment with the provided index.
        Parameters:
        index - the index (which must be smaller than size).
        Returns:
        The KeyType instance found on the provided position.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index was smaller than 0 or greater than size.

      • append

        <X extends Path<S>> X append(S aKey)
        Appends the provided KeyType to this Path, returning the resulting Path. Note that the returned value could/should be a new Path subtype instance, given that the implementation's internal state is immutable.
        Type Parameters:
        X - The explicit Path subtype.
        Parameters:
        aKey - The KeyType to append to this Path.
        Returns:
        The Path result from appending the provided KeyType instance to this Path. Note that the returned value could/should be a new Path subtype, given that the implementation's internal state is immutable.
